To secure important system files, you need to set the correct permissions.

1. Set permissions on /etc/ssh/sshd_config:
sudo chmod 600 /etc/ssh/sshd_config
sudo chown root:root /etc/ssh/sshd_config

2.Set permissions on /etc/passwd and /etc/shadow:
sudo chmod 644 /etc/passwd
sudo chmod 600 /etc/shadow
